07/11/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Trade union leaders in the state-owned railway company Caile Ferate Romane (CFR) announced on Thursday (November 6th) that after talks with Transport Minister Ludovic Orban, workers have decided to postpone by two weeks a warning strike they had planned for Friday. Trains will run according to normal schedules. The CFR says discussions with Orban resulted in agreements on four major issues involving workers. (Evenimentul Zilei - 07/11/08; Ziare.com, Mediafax - 06/11/08 
